Privacy Policy

Last Updated: November 14, 2024

Welcome to the Sri Lanka Aikido Association’s website. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting the personal information you share with us. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and protection of your information when you visit our website at https://lahiruprabodha.github.io/aikido.

1. Information We Collect
We collect information from you to enhance your experience with our website and to communicate with you effectively. Information we collect includes:

Personal Information: If you contact us through our website, we may collect your name, email address, and phone number.

Usage Data: We collect non-identifiable data, such as your IP address, browser type, pages visited, and duration of your visit. This helps us analyze and improve our website.

Cookies: Our website uses cookies to remember your preferences and to provide a better browsing experience. You can manage or disable cookies through your browser settings.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information for purposes including but not limited to:

Responding to inquiries and providing information about classes and events.
Improving our website and services.
Analyzing site traffic and user behavior to optimize user experience.
Managing promotional activities, including sharing updates on new classes and events (if you have opted in to receive these).
3. Sharing Your Information
Your information will not be sold, rented, or shared with third parties, except:

With your consent.
When required by law or to comply with legal processes.
To trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website (such as hosting services). These providers are required to keep your information confidential and use it solely for our benefit.
4. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, please be aware that no method of internet transmission is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.

5. Third-Party Links
Our website may contain links to external websites, including social media platforms. These third-party sites have separate and independent privacy policies, and we are not responsible for their content or privacy practices. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any linked sites.

6. Children’s Privacy
Our website is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information promptly.

7. Your Choices and Rights
Access and Correction: You may contact us to update or correct your personal information.

Opt-Out: If you no longer wish to receive updates or communications from us, you can unsubscribe by following the instructions provided in the communication or by contacting us directly.

Cookies: You can adjust your browser settings to disable cookies or to alert you when cookies are being used. Disabling cookies may affect your experience on our website.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will post the updated policy on this page with the "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of our website after changes have been posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.

